SUMMARIZER="E">         

Clarence Thomas, nominee to the Supreme Court, was brought up in
segregated Georgia.  He was abandoned by his father and lived with his
grandparents who educated him in a Catholic school of nuns.

Thomas became a believer in personal strength and individualism over
government activism, in effect, a black conservative.  He opposes
abortion rights, quotas and busing.

Thomas was educated at Holy Cross College, graduating in 1971, and
Yale Law School in 1974.  He worked as a lawyer in Missouri and was
appointed judge of the U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in 1990.  Thomas
is married and has one son.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d13"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="AP900306-0105"
