SUMMARIZER="E">         

Clarence Thomas was confirmed as a federal appeals judge on 6 March
1990.  He will be a judge on the U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in the
District of Columbia.

Complaints from liberals and senior citizens were ignored during the
confirmation.

Thomas was chairman of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission
under Reagan and Bush.  He is a critic of affirmative action and
quotas.

Thomas was born into poverty in Georgia.  He worked his way through
college and completed Yale law school.  Before his tenure on the
Commission, he worked for Senator Danforth, a strong Thomas supporter,
as a lawyer.</SUM>

